OL,6,FThe Supreme Court ruled that his
OL,7,Fdetention was unlawful because the
OL,8,Finterim custody order (ICO) used to
OL,9,Finitially detain him had not been
OL,10,F"considered personally" by then
OL,11,Fsecretary of state for Northern
OL,12,FIreland Willie Whitelaw.
OL,14,FAt the time of the case, the previous
OL,15,Fgovernment contended that the ICOs
OL,16,Fwere lawful due to a long-standing
OL,17,Fconvention, known as the Carltona
OL,18,Fprinciple, where officials and junior
OL,19,Fministers routinely act in the name of
OL,20,Fthe Secretary of State.
