OL,6,FMr Adams subsequently successfully
OL,7,Fchallenged a decision to deny an
OL,8,Fapplication for compensation for his
OL,9,Fdetention.
OL,11,FHowever, the Legacy Act stopped such
OL,12,Fpayouts to Mr Adams and other former
OL,13,Finternees, and retrospectively
OL,14,Fvalidated the ICOs to make them lawful
OL,15,Fand halted civil claims related to the
OL,16,Forders.
OL,18,FAt the time, the then UK government
OL,19,Fsaid the legislation would prevent up
OL,20,Fto 400 compensation bids by former
OL,21,Finternees.
